Since the Wisconsin Education Association never asked for the power of collective bargaining, the association's leadership was clueless on how to leverage it after the Municipal Employee Relations Act became law. (Note: for the politically astute, the Municipal Employee Relations Act of 1959 was the law Governor Scott Walker contentiously scaled back in 2011, an unpopular move that forced him to face a recall election that he won in 2012).
